data.text:
VS The original cognac created in the French region of Cognac, with its name restores the memory of Prince Joseph Poniatowski, Polish general and Commander-in-Chief of the Polish Army of the Warsaw Principality

The specific cult of the figure of Prince Joseph is the Polish version of the Napoleonic legend. It is a beverage full of subtle aromas with a brownish amber color. Its noble taste makes it an aristocrat among alcohols.
